condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Project Implementation Arrangement | Description :Each Project Implementing Entity shall maintain a ProvincialProject Leading Group or a Provincial Project Coordinating Group, a Provincial Project Management Office, and a County ProjectManagement Office. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Implementation Plan | Description :Each Project Implementing Entity shall carry out and caused to becarried out its activities under the Project in accordance with the Project Implementation Plan. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Operation and Maintenance Plan | Description :Each Project Implementing Entity shall ensure a properoperation and maintenance plan of each Sub-project carried out under the Project be prepared and agreed by the Bank at least threemonths prior to its completion, and thereafter, ensure the prompt implementation of each such plan. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Safeguards Framework-ECOP and PMP | Description :Each Project Implementing Entity shall implement or cause to beimplemented its ECOP and PMP in a manner satisfactory to the Bank.In addition, Gansu should also implement its EMDP, and Hunanimplement its respective EMP. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Safeguards Framework-RAP | Description :Each Project Implementing Entity shall, apply and caused to be appliedthe measures and actions set forth in its RAP in a timely and efficient manner satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Safeguards Instruments | Description :A Project Implementing Entity shall obtain the written approval toamending, suspending, or waiving its RAP, ECOP, PMP, or EMDP, orany provision thereof. | Frequency :Yearly
